+   <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.  */
+
+/* When the translation unit is compiled with -mfma (i.e. __FMA__ is
+   defined), GCC and clang lower __builtin_fma / __builtin_fmaf to a
+   single vfmadd* instruction.  In that case the 1200+ byte software
+   implementation in sysdeps/ieee754/dbl-64/s_fma.c is pure dead code:
+   collapse it to the builtin so the function shrinks from ~1.2 KiB to
+   6 bytes (one vfmadd213sd + ret).
+
+   The condition is per-translation-unit safe.  Multiarch wrappers such
+   as sysdeps/x86_64/fpu/multiarch/s_fma.c that build a __fma_sse2
+   fallback do so without -mfma in their per-file CFLAGS, so __FMA__
+   is undefined for that TU and USE_FMA_BUILTIN evaluates to 0 — the
+   software path is kept for hardware that lacks FMA, exactly as
+   today.
+
+   Pattern modelled on the existing
+   sysdeps/x86_64/fpu/math-use-builtins-trunc.h header which gates
+   USE_TRUNC_BUILTIN on __SSE4_1__ in the same per-TU manner.  */
+
+#ifdef __FMA__
+# define USE_FMA_BUILTIN  1
+# define USE_FMAF_BUILTIN 1
+#else
+# define USE_FMA_BUILTIN  0
+# define USE_FMAF_BUILTIN 0
+#endif
+
+#define USE_FMAL_BUILTIN     0
+#define USE_FMAF128_BUILTIN  0
